Custom Map Charts

Use a custom map if you have data with a geographical component that doesn't match any of the standard maps provided by CRM Analytics charts, such as custom regions. You can also use custom maps for areas that can be represented with polygons, such as stadium seat sections, city blocks, or floor plans.

Create a Custom Map

CRM Analytics comes with prepackaged maps that you can use in map, bubble map, and geo map. To create a custom map:

* Create a new map from the GeoJSON data
* Define the bounding box coordinates to zoom in on the area of interest
* Use the "id" property to match values between the data and the GeoJSON feature blocks

GeoJSON Structure

Standard GeoJSON typically has a structure that contains feature blocks similar to the following:


{
    "type": "Feature",
    "geometry": {
        "type": "MultiPolygon",
        "coordinates": [
            [125.6, 10.1],
            [126.1, 11.0], ...
        ]
    },
    "id": "SI",
    "properties": {
        "name": "Sandwich Islands",
        "property1": "value1"
    }
}

Each feature block defines a shape, or map area. To correctly overlay data onto the map, the data must have a column with values uniquely matching one of the properties in the GeoJSON.

Bounding Boxes

You can set the bounding box while creating or editing a map. This limits the map to the shapes within the coordinates, or borders, of the bounding box. When you create a map from a GeoJSON without a bounding box, every defined shape is displayed as an area on the map.
